<body>

<div id=3D"container">

<div id=3D"location"><a href=3D"https://mrieppel.net/index.html">Home</a> &=
gt; <a href=3D"https://mrieppel.net/etc/index.html">Etc</a> &gt; <a href=3D=
"https://mrieppel.net/prog/truthtable.html">Truth Table Generator</a></div>

<div id=3D"githublink"><a href=3D"https://github.com/mrieppel/TruthTableGen=
erator"><img src=3D"https://mrieppel.net/prog/github.png" style=3D"height:2=
5px;"></a></div>

<div id=3D"title">Truth Table Generator</div>

<p>This page contains a program that will generate truth tables for formula=
s of propositional logic.  You can enter multiple formulas separated by com=
mas to include more than one formula in a single table (e.g. to test for en=
tailment).  Below you can select which symbols to use for the truth-values =
and connectives, the style of the table (full table, main connective only, =
plain text, or <a href=3D"http://www.latex-project.org/">LaTeX</a> output),=
 and (by special request!) two-valued or different types of three-valued ta=
bles.</p>

<div id=3D"ttinput">
  <input type=3D"text" id=3D"in" size=3D"40">
  <input type=3D"button" value=3D"Generate Table">
</div>

<div id=3D"tt"></div>

<div id=3D"in-op">

<div id=3D"in-op1">
<div>Truth-Values:</div>
<input type=3D"radio" id=3D"tv1" name=3D"tvstyle" value=3D"tf" checked=3D""=
><label for=3D"tv1">T/F</label><br>
<input type=3D"radio" id=3D"tv2" name=3D"tvstyle" value=3D"tb"><label for=
=3D"tv2">=E2=8A=A4/=E2=8A=A5</label><br>
<input type=3D"radio" id=3D"tv3" name=3D"tvstyle" value=3D"oz"><label for=
=3D"tv3">1/0</label><br>
</div>

<div id=3D"in-op2">
<div>Connectives:</div>
<input type=3D"radio" id=3D"cn1" name=3D"cset" value=3D"cs1" checked=3D""><=
label for=3D"cn1">=C2=AC, =E2=88=A7, =E2=88=A8, =E2=86=92, =E2=86=94</label=
><br>
<input type=3D"radio" id=3D"cn2" name=3D"cset" value=3D"cs2"><label for=3D"=
cn2">~, &amp;, =E2=88=A8, =E2=86=92, =E2=86=94</label><br>
<input type=3D"radio" id=3D"cn3" name=3D"cset" value=3D"cs3"><label for=3D"=
cn3">~, &amp;, =E2=88=A8, =E2=8A=83, =E2=89=A1</label><br>
</div>

<div id=3D"in-op3">
<div>Table Style:</div>
<input type=3D"radio" name=3D"style" id=3D"full" value=3D"full" checked=3D"=
"><label for=3D"full">Full Table</label><br>
<input type=3D"radio" name=3D"style" id=3D"main" value=3D"main"><label for=
=3D"main">Main Connective</label><br>
<input type=3D"radio" name=3D"style" id=3D"text" value=3D"text"><label for=
=3D"text"><label for=3D"full">Text Table</label><br>
<input type=3D"radio" name=3D"style" id=3D"latex" value=3D"latex"><label fo=
r=3D"latex">LaTex Table</label><br>
</label></div>

<div id=3D"in-op4">
<div>Type:</div>
<input type=3D"radio" name=3D"type" id=3D"twoval" value=3D"twoval" checked=
=3D""><label for=3D"twoval">Two-Valued</label><br>
<input type=3D"radio" name=3D"type" id=3D"luka" value=3D"luka"><label for=
=3D"luka">=C5=81ukasiewicz</label><br>
<input type=3D"radio" name=3D"type" id=3D"skleen" value=3D"skleen"><label f=
or=3D"skleen"><label for=3D"full">Strong Kleene</label><br>
<input type=3D"radio" name=3D"type" id=3D"wkleen" value=3D"wkleen"><label f=
or=3D"wkleen">Weak Kleene</label><br>
</label></div>

</div>
<br>


<p><b>Symbols:</b> use the following keyboard symbols in your input for the=
 various logical connectives:</p>


<table>
<tbody><tr><td class=3D"connective">~</td><td>for negation</td></tr>
<tr><td class=3D"connective">&amp;</td><td>for conjunction</td></tr>
<tr><td class=3D"connective">v</td><td>for disjunction</td></tr>
<tr><td class=3D"connective">&gt;</td><td>for the conditional</td></tr>
<tr><td class=3D"connective">&lt; &gt;</td><td>for the biconditional</td></=
tr>
<tr><td class=3D"connective">#</td><td>for absurdity/falsum</td></tr>
<tr><td class=3D"connective">|</td><td>for NAND (aka the <a href=3D"https:/=
/mrieppel.net/prog/sheffer.html">Sheffer Stroke</a>)</td></tr>
<tr><td class=3D"connective">!</td><td>for NOR (Wittgenstein's <a href=3D"h=
ttps://mrieppel.net/prog/sheffer.html">Sheffer Stroke</a>)</td></tr>
</tbody></table>

<br>
<p>Here are some examples of well-formed inputs the program will accept:</p=
>

<ul style=3D"list-style-type:none;padding:0;">
<li>~A</li>
<li>(A &amp; B)</li>
<li>(A &amp; (~B &gt; C))</li>
<li>(# &gt; (B v ~A))</li>
<li>(A|B) &lt;&gt; ~(A &amp; B)</li>
<li>(A &lt;&gt; (B v C)), A, (~B &gt; C)</li>
</ul>

<p>The source code is available on GitHub, just click the icon at the top r=
ight corner of the page.

</p><footer>=C2=A9 2010-2024 Michael Rieppel</footer>

</div>
